<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--BentonCelebration     04-16 0120</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Benton Celebration,0123</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thomas Hart Benton's Hometown Celebrates His Birthday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEOSHO, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small town reconciled some differences with
its most famous son Saturday as residents turned out to mark the
100th anniversary of the birth of muralist Thomas Hart Benton.
   Benton, one of the most famous American muralists of the 1930s
and 1940s, was viewed with suspicion growing up in Neosho in the
1890s. Locals thought him egotistical, and he left the town at age
17 to start his painting career.
   The ceremony began with a party Friday night at Crowder College.
   On Saturday, the actual birthdate, a show of 55 Benton
lithographs opened in four financial institutions in downtown
Neosho.
   Neosho's population is about 9,000.
</TEXT>
